{"sections":{"main":{"type":"main-article","disabled":true,"settings":{"color_scheme":"scheme-2","show_image":true,"enable_parallax":true,"image_size":"medium","content_width":"xs","show_date":false,"show_category":false,"show_author":false,"show_share_buttons":false,"show_sticky_bar":false,"toolbar_color_scheme":""}},"image_with_text_7cHCBe":{"type":"image-with-text","blocks":{"richtext_ynn8c3":{"type":"richtext","settings":{"content":"<h3><strong>PIGEON, STILTON & WALUT SALAD<\/strong><\/h3>"}}},"block_order":["richtext_ynn8c3"],"settings":{"color_scheme":"scheme-2","separate_section_with_border":false,"image":"shopify:\/\/shop_images\/PIGEON_SALAD_FINE_WILD.jpg","reveal_on_scroll":true,"image_position":"end","content_width":"sm","remove_vertical_spacing":true}},"rich_text_qapXHx":{"type":"rich-text","blocks":{"subheading_Y78fAJ":{"type":"subheading","settings":{"text":"<strong>Servings:<\/strong> 2  <strong>Prep Time:<\/strong> 10 Minutes <strong>Cook Time<\/strong>: 15 Minutes <strong>Total Time: <\/strong>25 Minutes "}}},"block_order":["subheading_Y78fAJ"],"settings":{"color_scheme":"scheme-2","separate_section_with_border":false,"content_width":"sm","text_position":"center","remove_vertical_spacing":false}},"rich_text_cXPwW7":{"type":"rich-text","blocks":{"heading_AJMbTn":{"type":"heading","settings":{"text":"<strong>INGREDIENTS<\/strong>","heading_tag":"h4"}},"richtext_xXJnzy":{"type":"richtext","settings":{"content":"<ul><li>1 Squab Pigeon, prepared and cooked as per <a href=\"https:\/\/www.fineandwild.com\/blogs\/recipes\/how-to-cook-squab-pigeon\">Squab Pigeon Preparation & Cooking Tips<\/a><\/li><li>100g of mixed salad leaves, such as baby radicchio and red endive, washed and dried<\/li><li>30g walnuts, toasted<\/li><li>40g Stilton, we used Colston Basset, crumbled<\/li><\/ul>"}},"heading_3aqUka":{"type":"heading","settings":{"text":"<strong>DRESSING<\/strong>","heading_tag":"h4"}},"richtext_HnHtXq":{"type":"richtext","settings":{"content":"<ul><li>1 tablespoon sherry vinegar<\/li><li>1 tablespoon red wine vinegar<\/li><li>1\/2 teaspoon Dijon mustard<\/li><li>1\/2 - 1 teaspoon of honey to taste<\/li><li>6 tablespoons of light olive oil (not extra virgin)<\/li><\/ul>"}}},"block_order":["heading_AJMbTn","richtext_xXJnzy","heading_3aqUka","richtext_HnHtXq"],"settings":{"color_scheme":"scheme-2","separate_section_with_border":true,"content_width":"sm","text_position":"center","remove_vertical_spacing":false}},"rich_text_znVA7E":{"type":"rich-text","blocks":{"heading_F6BnFW":{"type":"heading","settings":{"text":"<strong>METHOD<\/strong>","heading_tag":"h4"}},"subheading_EBUadW":{"type":"subheading","settings":{"text":"<strong>STEP ONE<\/strong>"}},"richtext_wCyiME":{"type":"richtext","settings":{"content":"<p>Roast the pigeon on the crown, when rested, remove the breasts and slice each one into 4 pieces.<\/p>"}},"subheading_rtg7rg":{"type":"subheading","settings":{"text":"<strong>STEP TWO<\/strong>"}},"richtext_EzcbYM":{"type":"richtext","settings":{"content":"<p>While the pigeon is resting, prepare the dressing by whisking all the ingredients together in a bowl.<\/p>"}},"subheading_Uge4wP":{"type":"subheading","settings":{"text":"<strong>STEP THREE<\/strong>"}},"richtext_xaPaMA":{"type":"richtext","settings":{"content":"<p>When ready to serve, place the salad leaves in a bowl and add enough dressing to lightly coat the leaves. Add the walnuts, Stilton and pigeon slices, gently stir once to incorporate.<\/p><p>Divide the salad between two plates and drizzle over a little extra dressing. Serve immediately.<\/p>"}}},"block_order":["heading_F6BnFW","subheading_EBUadW","richtext_wCyiME","subheading_rtg7rg","richtext_EzcbYM","subheading_Uge4wP","richtext_xaPaMA"],"settings":{"color_scheme":"scheme-2","separate_section_with_border":false,"content_width":"sm","text_position":"center","remove_vertical_spacing":false}},"image_with_text_x7nYNT":{"type":"image-with-text","blocks":{"heading_brqyyJ":{"type":"heading","settings":{"tex